<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="63">
[[ 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3EC083FF-2C57-4D7E-BEF2-8D82876871DF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Metahomaloptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Metahomaloptera Chang 1944:54" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="63" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Metahomaloptera Chang</taxonomicName>
]]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="63">
The hillstream loach genus 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3EC083FF-2C57-4D7E-BEF2-8D82876871DF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Metahomaloptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Metahomaloptera Chang 1944:54" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="63" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Metahomaloptera</taxonomicName>
was erected by Chang (1944), with 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9DFCE4AC-0CCB-4DBF-8B6F-EB7E9729F36E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Metahomaloptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Metahomaloptera omeiensis Chang 1944:54" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="63" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="omeiensis">M. omeiensis</taxonomicName>
as the type species. Chang (1944) identified 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3EC083FF-2C57-4D7E-BEF2-8D82876871DF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Metahomaloptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Metahomaloptera Chang 1944:54" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="63" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Metahomaloptera</taxonomicName>
using the following characters: “head and anterior part of body greatly depressed and ventrally flattened; snout broad, rounded, and trenchant; eye superolateral, with free orbital margin; mouth inferior, crescent-shaped, and of moderate size, with 8 barbels, 4 rostral and 4 maxillary; upper lip narrow, with single row of papillae; both jaws provided with sharp horny edges; gill-opening very small, crescent-shaped, situated entirely above the base of pectoral; pectoral fin with 20-23 rays; pelvic fin with 17-21 rays.” Xie, et al. (1984) described a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9DFCE4AC-0CCB-4DBF-8B6F-EB7E9729F36E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Metahomaloptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Metahomaloptera omeiensis Chang 1944:54" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="63" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="omeiensis">Metahomaloptera omeiensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AE810F0F-1D7C-4920-97E2-854471185773" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Metahomaloptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Metahomaloptera omeiensis hangshuiensis Xie, Yang &amp; Gong 1984:63" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="63" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="omeiensis" subSpecies="hangshuiensis">M. o. hangshuiensis</taxonomicName>
, from a tributary of the upper Yangtse River. At present, only one species of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3EC083FF-2C57-4D7E-BEF2-8D82876871DF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Metahomaloptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Metahomaloptera Chang 1944:54" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="63" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Metahomaloptera</taxonomicName>
has been recorded from the upper Yangtse River. Chen (1990) recorded 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Metahomaloptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="63" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="omeiensis" subSpecies="omeiensis">M. omeiensis omeiensis</taxonomicName>
in Yanjin and Weixin, Yunnan Province, China. He also added a note regarding a specimen of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3EC083FF-2C57-4D7E-BEF2-8D82876871DF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Metahomaloptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Metahomaloptera Chang 1944:54" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="63" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Metahomaloptera</taxonomicName>
collected in Fumin County, Yunnan, China, and listed some differences between this specimen and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Balitoridae" genus="Metahomaloptera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageNumber="63" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="omeiensis" subSpecies="omeiensis">M. omeiensis omeiensis</taxonomicName>
, but lacking enough material, did not describe it as a new species.
</paragraph>
